-- Brazilian Stock Movers: Tele Norte Leste, Gol, Tam, Petrobras
-- B y   Z a c h a r y   T r a c e r
-- 2011-12-28T20:40:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-28/brazilian-stock-movers-tele-norte-leste-gol-tam-petrobras.html
The following companies had  unusual (IBOV) 
price changes in Sao Paulo trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close of trading. Preferred
shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The Bovespa Index fell 2.5 percent to 56,533.76.  Tele Norte Leste Participacoes SA  (TNLP4 BS) declined 2.9
percent to 17.33 reais. The company was cut to “market
perform” from “outperform” at Bradesco Corretora.  Gol Linhas Aereas Inteligentes SA  (GOLL4 BS),  Brazil ’s
second-biggest airline by market value, retreated 6.4 percent to
11.91 reais. Brazil’s civil aviation authority wants to change
rules to stimulate competition and lower ticket prices, said
Marcelo Guaranys, the agency’s president. Rival  Tam SA  (TAMM4
BS) fell 2.3 percent to 35.67 reais.  Petroleo Brasileiro SA  (PETR4 BS) dropped 3.5 percent to
21.43 reais. Oil fell, ending six days of gains, as concerns
eased that  Iran  may block shipments through the  Strait of Hormuz 
at the mouth of the  Persian Gulf .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zachary Tracer in New York at 
